{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.28",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 28,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 28",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 28 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:1",
      "text": "For there is a place for the silver, whence it comes, and a place for the gold, whence it is refined.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:2",
      "text": "For iron comes out of the earth, and brass is hewn out like stone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:3",
      "text": "He has set a bound to darkness, and he searches out every limit: a stone is darkness, and the shadow of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:4",
      "text": "There is a cutting off of the torrent by reason of dust: so they that forget the right way are weakened; they are removed from among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:5",
      "text": "As for the earth, out of it shall come bread: under it has been turned up as it were fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:6",
      "text": "Her stones are the place of the sapphire: and her dust supplies man with gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:7",
      "text": "There is a path, the fowl has not known it, neither has the eye of the vulture seen it:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:8",
      "text": "neither have the sons of the proud trodden it, a lion has not passed upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:9",
      "text": "He has stretched forth his hand on the sharp rock, and turned up mountains by the roots:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:10",
      "text": "and he has interrupted the whirlpools of rivers, and mine eye has seen every precious thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:11",
      "text": "And he has laid bare the depths of rivers, and has brought his power to light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:12",
      "text": "But whence has wisdom been discovered? and what is the place of knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:13",
      "text": "A mortal has not known its way, neither indeed has it been discovered among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:14",
      "text": "The depth said, It is not in me: and the sea said, It is not with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:15",
      "text": "One shall not give fine gold instead of it, neither shall silver be weighed in exchange for it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:16",
      "text": "Neither shall it be compared with gold of Sophir, with the precious onyx and sapphire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:17",
      "text": "Gold and crystal shall not be equalled to it, neither shall vessels of gold be its exchange.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:18",
      "text": "Coral and fine pearl shall not be mentioned: but do thou esteem wisdom above the most precious things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:19",
      "text": "The topaz of Ethiopia shall not be equalled to it; it shall not be compared with pure gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:20",
      "text": "Whence then is wisdom found? and of what kind is the place of understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:21",
      "text": "It has escaped the notice of every man, and has been hidden from the birds of the sky.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:22",
      "text": "Destruction and Death said, We have heard the report of it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:23",
      "text": "God has well ordered the way of it, and he knows the place of it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:24",
      "text": "For he surveys the whole earth under heaven, knowing the things in the earth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:25",
      "text": "all that he has made; the weight of the winds, the measures of the water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:26",
      "text": "When he made them, thus he saw and numbered them, and made a way for the pealing of the thunder.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:27",
      "text": "Then he saw it, and declared it: he prepared it and traced it out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.28.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:28",
      "text": "And he said to man, Behold, godliness is wisdom; and to abstain from evil is understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
